msgid "Options Unique to the Color Smudge Brush"
msgstr "色ぼかしブラシの独特なオプション"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:53
msgid "Color Rate"
msgstr "描画色の割合"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:55
msgid ""
"How much of the foreground color is added to the smudging mix. Works "
"together with :ref:`option_smudge_length` and :ref:`option_smudge_radius`."
msgstr ""
"ぼかす描画色の割合を指します。:ref:`option_smudge_length` "
"と :ref:`option_smudge_radius` と連携して機能します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:59
msgid ".. image:: /images/brushes/colorsmudge/brushengine_color_rate_smear.svg"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:59
msgid ""
"A variety of color smudge strokes in the :dfn:`Smear Mode` with different "
"opacities, smudge lengths and spacing. All are with 50% :dfn:`Color Rate`. "
"Left-hand set being the old algorithm and the right-hand set the new "
"algorithm. The bottom two strokes are using the :ref:`bm_color_dodge` "
"blending mode."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:63
msgid ""
"The option :guilabel:`Use new smudge algorithm` greatly affects how "
"the :dfn:`Color Rate` works. With the old algorithm, the :dfn:`Color Rate` "
"will be affected by both smudge length and opacity, while with the new "
"algorithm, :dfn:`Color Rate` will only interact with :dfn:`Opacity`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:65
msgid ""
"At first glance, this may seem like it reduces nuance. But instead, the new "
"algorithm simplifies brush creation, with it being far clearer which "
"elements interact with :dfn:`Color Rate`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:69
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/brushes/colorsmudge/brushengine_color_rate_dulling.svg"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:69
msgid "Same as figure above, but then in :dfn:`Dulling Mode`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:71
msgid ""
"Using the new algorithm, turning off the smudge length is all that's needed "
"to make a brush that is similar to the :ref:`pixel_brush_engine`. This is "
"useful as a starting point for brushes that only need a little smudge."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:73
msgid ""
"When using the :ref:`gradient mode <brush_mode>`, the :dfn:`Color Rate` will "
"control the colored brush tip instead of a flat color."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:75
msgid ""
"Blending modes are applied when the color part is composed onto the smudge "
"part. This effectively means that color smudge brushes with a blending mode "
"other than :ref:`bm_normal` will be greatly affected by :dfn:`Color Rate` in "
"addition to :ref:`option_spacing` and :ref:`opacity <option_opacity_n_flow>`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:80
msgid "Smudge Length"
msgstr "混色の持続"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:82
msgid ""
"Affects smudging and allows you to set it to Sensors. Smudging is greatly "
"affected by :ref:`option_spacing` as well as :ref:`Opacity "
"<option_opacity_n_flow>`. The former controls how many dabs are placed, and "
"thus how many samples are made. This results in a smoother result "
"for :dfn:`Smear Mode`, and a more opaque result for :dfn:`Dulling Mode`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:84
msgid "There are two major types:"
msgstr "主要な2つのタイプを示します:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:87
msgid ""
"Copies the area underneath the previous position of the brush onto the new "
"position, taking opacity into account. This tends to result in a smear-"
"effect."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:89
msgid ""
"Great for making brushes that have a very impasto oil feel to them. It's "
"recommended to have a low spacing for Smear, as this will result in a less "
"grainy looking smear."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:93
msgid "Smearing"
msgstr "色をのばす"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:93
msgid ""
"A variety of color smudge strokes in the :dfn:`Smear Mode` with different "
"opacities, smudge lengths and spacing. Left-hand set being the old algorithm "
"and the right-hand set the new algorithm. The bottom two strokes are using "
"the :ref:`bm_color_dodge` blending mode, which does not have any meaningful "
"effect, given the :ref:`option_color_rate` is set to 0%."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:96
msgid ""
"Picks the color underneath the brush dab (using the Smudge Radius, if "
"applicable), and first fills the whole dab with that before applying the "
"color and the opacity. Named so because it dulls strong colors."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:98
msgid ""
"Using an arithmetic blending type, Dulling is great for more smooth type of "
"painting. It's recommended to increase the spacing on dulling brushes as "
"much as possible without the stroke looking choppy, as it speeds up the "
"brush without losing smudge quality. The resulting stroke can be made "
"stronger by increasing the smudge radius or the opacity."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:102
msgid "Dulling"
msgstr "混色して描画"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:102
msgid "Same as above, but then for the :dfn:`Dulling Mode`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:104
msgid "Strength"
msgstr "強度"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:105
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Affects how much the smudge length takes from the previous dab its "
#| "sampling. This means that smudge-length at 1.0 will never decrease, but "
#| "smudge-lengths under that will decrease based on spacing and opacity/flow."
msgid ""
"Affects how much the smudge length takes from the previous dab its sampling. "
"This means that smudge length at 100% will never decrease, but smudge "
"lengths under that will decrease based on :ref:`option_spacing` "
"and :ref:`Opacity <option_opacity_n_flow>`."
msgstr ""
"直前の描点から伸びる混色する長さに影響します。1.0に設定した時の混色の持続する"
"長さは減ることはなく、不透明度や流量、間隔によって減らせることを意味していま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:107
msgid ""
"Controls whether the transparency of the smeared pixels is taken into "
"account when painting. This can be helpful to get a more opaque effect, as "
"if laying down thick layers of paint, without losing the smudge effect."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:111
msgid "Different strokes showing how smear alpha functions."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:113
msgid ":dfn:`Smear Mode` with :dfn:`Smear Alpha`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:114
msgid ":dfn:`Smear Mode` without :dfn:`Smear Alpha`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:115
msgid ":dfn:`Dulling Mode` with :dfn:`Smear Alpha`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:116
msgid ":dfn:`Dulling Mode` without :dfn:`Smear Alpha`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:117
msgid "Smear Alpha"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:117
msgid ""
":dfn:`Dulling Mode` without :dfn:`Smear Alpha`, "
"and :ref:`option_smudge_radius` set to 100%."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:122
msgid "Use new smudge algorithm"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:122
msgid ""
"The new smudge algorithm was initially introduced to allow :ref:`lightness "
"and gradient modes <brush_mode>` on the color smudge. But it allows for "
"more: it is a little quicker, and it has a better separation between "
"the :ref:`option_color_rate` and the :dfn:`Smudge Length`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:125
msgid "Common behaviors:"
msgstr "共通動作:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:127
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Unchecking the smudge rate function sets smudge rate to 1.00 (not 0.00)."
msgid ""
"Unchecking the smudge length function sets smudge length to 100% (not 0.00)."
msgstr ""
"ぼかし半径の機能のチェックを外すと、ぼかし半径は1.00に設定されます。(0.00では"
"ありません)"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:128
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Opacity: Below 0.50, there is practically no smudging left: keep opacity "
#| "over 0.50."
msgid ""
"Opacity: Below 50%, there is practically no smudging left: keep opacity over "
"50%."
msgstr ""
"不透明度が0.50以下では、不透明度はぼかしはほとんど効きません。0.50以上に設定"
"してください。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:131
msgid "Differences:"
msgstr "違い:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:133
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Spacing with Smearing: the lower the spacing, the smoother the effect, so "
#| "for smearing with a round brush you may prefer a value of 0.05 or less. "
#| "Spacing affects the length of the smudge trail, but to a much lesser "
#| "extent. The \"strength\" of the effect remains more or less the same "
#| "however."
msgid ""
"Spacing with Smearing: the lower the spacing, the smoother the effect, so "
"for smearing with a round brush you may prefer a value of 0.05 or less. "
"Spacing affects the length of the smudge trail, but to a much lesser extent. "
"The :guilabel:`strength` of the effect remains more or less the same however."
msgstr ""
"間隔と色のばし: 間隔が小さいほど効果は滑らかになるため、円形ブラシで色のばし"
"を使うときは値を0.05以下に設定すると良いでしょう。間隔はぼかし軌跡の長さに影"
"響しますが、程度はかなり小さいです。しかしながら、効果の「強さ」は同程度残り"
"ます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:134
msgid ""
"Spacing with Dulling: the lower the spacing, the stronger the effect: "
"lowering the spacing too much can make the dulling effect too strong (it "
"picks up a color and never lets go of it). The length of the effect is also "
"affected."
msgstr ""
"間隔と混色: 間隔が小さいほど、効果は強くなります: 間隔を小さくしすぎると混色"
"効果が強くなりすぎます(拾った色を決して手放しません)。効果の長さには影響しま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:135
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Both Smearing and Dulling have a \"smudge trail\", but in the case of "
#| "Dulling, the brush shape is preserved. Instead the trail determines how "
#| "fast the color it picked up is dropped off."
msgid ""
"Both Smearing and Dulling have a \"smudge trail\", but in the case of "
"Dulling, the brush shape is preserved. Instead, the trail determines how "
"fast the color it picked up is dropped off."
msgstr ""
"色のばし・混色どちらもぼかされた「混色された軌跡」を持ちますが、混色の場合に"
"は、ブラシ形状は保持されます。代わりに、混色された軌跡が拾った色を手放す速さ"
"を決定します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:140
msgid "Smudge Radius"
msgstr "混色範囲の半径"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:142
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Smudge Radius` allows you to sample a larger radius when "
"using smudge-length in :guilabel:`Dulling` mode."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`混色範囲の半径` は :guilabel:`混色して描画` モードで混色の持続設定"
"を使用する時に、より大きい半径で混色することを可能にします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:144
msgid ""
"The slider is percentage of the brush-size. You can have it modified "
"with :guilabel:`Sensors`."
msgstr ""
"スライダーはブラシサイズのパーセンテージを示します。:guilabel:`センサー` から"
"修正できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:148
msgid ".. image:: /images/brushes/colorsmudge/brushengine_smudge_radius.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:148
msgid ""
"A variety of brush strokes using 50% color rate, 50% smudge length and 50% "
"opacity, but different smudge radii. The top stroke is in :dfn:`smear mode` "
"and thus smudge radius is not in effect."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:152
msgid ""
"In versions prior to 5.0, Smudge Radius can go up to 3,00,00%, while the "
"program's internal value is 1/100 of the displayed value. Starting from 5.0, "
"the displayed and the internal value of Smudge Radius are unified, they can "
"only go up to 300%, as intended."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:157
msgid "Overlay"
msgstr "オーバーレイ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:159
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Overlay is a toggle that determine whether or not the smudge brush will "
#| "sample all layers (overlay on), or only the current one."
msgid ""
"Overlay is a toggle that determine whether the smudge brush will sample all "
"layers (overlay on), or only the current one."
msgstr ""
"オーバーレイは色ぼかしブラシが現在のレイヤーのみを対象とするか、あるいは全レ"
"イヤーを対象とするか(オーバーレイ:オン)を決定するトグルです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:161
msgid ""
"By default, the Color Smudge Brush only takes information from the layer it "
"is on. However, if you want it to take color information from all the "
"layers, you can turn on the Overlay mode."
msgstr ""
"デフォルトでは、色ぼかしブラシは現作業レイヤーの色情報を参照しますが、すべて"
"のレイヤーの色情報を参照したい場合には、合成モードをオンにすることができま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:163
msgid ""
"Be aware though, that it does so by \"picking up\" bits of the layer "
"underneath, which may mess up your drawing if you later make changes to the "
"layer underneath."
msgstr ""
"しかし、下にあるレイヤーから「拾い上げる」ことに注意してください。後から下に"
"あるレイヤーに変更を加えると絵が崩れてしまうかもしれません。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:168
msgid "Paint Thickness"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:172
msgid ""
"This affects how strong the :ref:`lightness modes <brush_mode>` affect the "
"current color. Because the :dfn:`Color Smudge Brush` smudges, what actually "
"happens is that the lightness part is painted into a separate height map. "
"This prevents the shadows and highlights of the current lightness brush tip "
"from being mixed into the smudge, which would have resulted in all smudges "
"becoming white or black. The height map is discarded when switching brush "
"engines, layers or tools. Because this heightmap only exists for the layer "
"currently being edited, lightness brushes and paint thickness cannot be used "
"together with :ref:`option_overlay`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:176
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/brushes/colorsmudge/"
"brushengine_paint_thickness_strength.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:176
msgid ""
"Image showing off different variations of :dfn:`Paint Thickness`, with the "
"top three strokes being in :dfn:`Smear Mode` and the bottom three "
"in :dfn:`Dulling Mode`. Strengths are 100%, 50%, and 0% from top to bottom."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:178
msgid ""
"This has two modes, which change how the existing heightmap is interpreted:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:180
msgid "Overwrite (Smooth out when low) existing paint thickness"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:181
msgid ""
"Here the lightness value of the brushstroke overrides the value that was "
"there before, effectively smoothing out previous paint if the thickness "
"value is low. The Opacity setting will cause it to blend with the previous "
"paint height, but that will also bring down the color. This mode is useful "
"for a brush that can paint with thickness, but can also smooth out existing "
"paint if you wish."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:183
msgid "Paint over existing paint thickness (controlled by smudge length)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:183
msgid ""
"Here the lightness value blends with the previous values, based on the "
"Smudge Length, as described above. It allows the kind of blending with "
"previous paint height that Opacity allows in the Overwrite mode, but without "
"affecting the color rate."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_engines/color_smudge_engine.rst:187
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/brushes/colorsmudge/brushengine_paint_thickness_type.svg"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
